overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire application, which they perceived as functional but lacking
  visual sophistication. The agent initiated a comprehensive review of the app's
  current styling, examining global CSS, layout, and individual UI components.
  Based on this analysis, a strategy was developed to introduce a calming,
  sleep-themed color palette, enhance typography, refine spacing, and improve
  the visual interest of form elements. The implementation involved updating
  globals.css with new color variables and utility classes, redesigning the
  QuestionnaireForm with subtle background effects and a more engaging progress
  bar, and overhauling the IntroSection with a hero element and feature cards.
  Furthermore, core UI components like checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders
  were polished, and section groupings were restyled to be more inviting. The
  ReportSection also received significant visual upgrades to align with the new
  theme. The outcome is an application with a more professional, calming, and
  cohesive aesthetic, specifically tailored to a sleep health experience.
